  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Receptionist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Receptionist</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are a dynamic company with 16 years in the beauty industry. We currently have 07 outlets across Singapore with 3 brands thus you will be introduced and expected to contribute to value add to the interesting marketing concepts suited for both the Beauty and Wellness industry.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· The candidate is expected to make outbound calls to customers and to respond to inbound enquiries from leads, giving a basic introduction of Company’s latest promotions with the aim of maximising the take-up of these promotions.</p>\n<p>· Respond to customer inquiries via phone, email, and chat in a timely and professional manner</p>\n<p>· Scheduling service appointments for customers and follow up</p>\n<p>· Identify and escalate complex issues to appropriate departments for resolution</p>\n<p>· Collaborate with team members to improve policies and customer service processes</p>\n<p>· Address customers’ complaints in a timely and professional manner. Conduct first level investigation into customers’ complaints, identify expectation gap and work with service team members on service recovery aiming towards customer satisfaction.</p>\n<p>· Build customer loyalty and retention by delivering the unique customer service experience</p>\n<p>· Update activity reports (Documentation of calls for tracking, monitoring and follow-up)</p>\n<p>· Maintain accurate records and reports on customer interactions and feedback</p>\n<p>· Strong teamwork and interpersonal skills to work effectively with colleagues.</p>\n<p>· Assist in ad hoc administrative duties</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Singaporean or PR Only</p>\n<p>· Must be able to converse fluently over the phone, and read and write in English and Chinese</p>\n<p>· Must be proficient in MS Word and MS Excel</p>\n<p>· At least 1 year customer service or telemarketing experience</p>\n<p>· Skilled in negotiation, listen attentively, identify callers’ needs, and remain composed even when dealing with agitated customers</p>\n<p>· Minimum GCE ‘N’ Level</p>\n<p>· Able to commit retail hours</p>\n<p>· Requires a sense of urgency</p>\n<p>· Able to work independently with minimal supervision</p>\n<p>· Good team player, positive attitude and willing to learn</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Up to $2800 monthly salary, depending on experience of candidate</p>\n<p>· 5 days work week (Retail hours)</p>\n<p>· Staff discounts and privileges from all Phoenix Rise outlets</p>\n<p>· Office located near Tai Seng MRT (Circle Line)</p>\n<p>Clean, quiet and comfortable working environment</p>",
